  "dataFlow": "A user (or the autonomy poller reading Linear) submits a repo URL + brief to POST /api/build. The FastAPI handler validates via Pydantic, checks the session concurrency cap, and creates a BuildSession object in the in-memory _sessions dict, simultaneously persisting it to disk via atomic os.replace(). A background asyncio task runs run_build(): it clones the repo to a sandboxed workspace, injects lesson context and skill files into the prompt, invokes the Claude Agent SDK (_run_claude_via_sdk) which streams JSON events back. Events are appended to session.output_lines and fanned out over the /ws/build/{sid} WebSocket and /api/sessions/{sid}/logs SSE endpoint to the browser. After generation, the evaluator SDK call grades the git diff on 4 dimensions; if the score meets the threshold the session advances to 'complete' and changes are pushed to GitHub via git. Session state and evaluator scores are written to Supabase (gate_checks table) via the fire-and-forget supabase_log.py writer. Separately, the cron engine dispatches Pi-SEO scanner jobs that clone portfolio repos, run pattern matching, and write scan JSON to .harness/scan-results/; the triage engine reads these and calls the Linear GraphQL API to create issues. The MCP server reads the same .harness/ files via the filesystem and exposes them as tools to Claude Desktop over stdio. Telegram inbound messages are written to .harness/telegram-inbox/ by the poller and drained by the watchdog, which routes them to self-heal actions, idea files, or Telegram replies.",
